      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, remove the pan from the heat and shred it apart with two forks – this technique is known as 'pulling'</p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat with the pulled chicken<strong> </strong>and add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>, <strong>soy sauce </strong>and 50ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [75ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml] </span><strong>cold</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>water</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until the chicken is coated in a sticky sauce – this is your <strong>pulled</strong> <strong>hoisin chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1692624867654-x200.jpg",
