            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, return the reserved pot to a medium heat with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced spring greens</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 1 min or until starting to wilt</p><p>Add a splash of<strong> water</strong> and cook, covered, for 2 min or until completely wilted, then stir in the <strong>drained noodles </strong>and<strong> toasted sesame oil</strong> – these are your <strong>sesame noodles</strong></p>",
